United States Secret Service Special Agent Nole Edward Remagen passed away after suffering a stroke while on duty in Scotland. He was surrounded by family and fellow Secret Service agents. Special Agent Remagen, a veteran of the United States Marines, had served with the Secret Service for 19 years and was part of the Presidential Protection Division. The article acknowledges his dedication and service to the nation, and expresses gratitude to the men and women of the Secret Service for their sacrifices and commitment to safety and security.